          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Self-Service API Key and Quota Provisioning"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Without a self-service provisioning system, every team that wants to integrate Claude must open a ticket, wait for a platform engineer to create an API key, manually communicate the key via an insecure channel, and set up a quota in a spreadsheet. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A self-service portal — accessible via the Internal Developer Portal or a CLI — lets teams provision their own Anthropic API key, workspace, and token quota in under two minutes, with the key stored securely in AWS Secrets Manager and the quota tracked in a central database."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Self-service API key provisioning flow: portal → approval gate → Anthropic API + Secrets Manager",
          "title": null
        }
